[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":449},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F12\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F12\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F12\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F12\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight\u002F":424,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F12\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight\u002F":433},"\u002Fother\u002F20230412\u002F77568631\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":405,"date":406,"description":407,"extension":408,"lang":409,"meta":410,"navigation":411,"path":412,"readingMinutes":413,"seo":414,"standalone":415,"stem":416,"tags":417,"tldr":421,"updated":406,"url":422,"__hash__":423},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight.md","Replace Mac's Built-In Spotlight With Raycast","1758632094",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":388},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,31,41,47,50,56,62,65,69,72,75,81,84,90,93,99,102,108,112,115,121,127,131,134,140,146,149,154,157,160,166,169,175,179,182,188,196,202,208,213,216,220,223,229,235,238,242,245,254,260,263,269,272,278,281,287,290,296,299,305,312,316,319,323,326],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Raycast is a Mac app that can fully replace Spotlight. Why \"fully\" replace? Because it's genuinely capable, and it supports custom commands and extensions for whatever you want it to do. Let me show you what I mean.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"installing-raycast","Installing Raycast",[17,25,26],{},[27,28],"img",{"alt":29,"src":30},"Raycast","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FMg5iDLf.png",[17,32,33,34,40],{},"Head over to ",[35,36,29],"a",{"href":37,"rel":38},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.raycast.com\u002F",[39],"nofollow"," and download it (macOS only for now). On first launch you'll see this welcome screen:",[17,42,43],{},[27,44],{"alt":45,"src":46},"Welcome to Raycast","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FRossH4S.png",[17,48,49],{},"Click \"Skip setup\" to jump straight into the main UI.",[17,51,52],{},[27,53],{"alt":54,"src":55},"Skip setup","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FiWRpmVM.png",[17,57,58],{},[27,59],{"alt":60,"src":61},"Raycast UI","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FFSSEgVl.png",[17,63,64],{},"Easy. And the look-and-feel is very close to Spotlight already.",[12,66,68],{"id":67},"changing-raycasts-hotkey","Changing Raycast's hotkey",[17,70,71],{},"By default Raycast opens with Option + Space. Since we're replacing Spotlight, we want Cmd + Space — that way Spotlight's hotkey works, just with Raycast underneath, and there's no conflict.",[17,73,74],{},"Open System Settings, click \"Keyboard\" (or search Spotlight), then \"Keyboard Shortcuts\":",[17,76,77],{},[27,78],{"alt":79,"src":80},"Keyboard Shortcuts","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGZEVQ5n.png",[17,82,83],{},"Find \"Spotlight\", uncheck \"Show Spotlight Search\", and click Done:",[17,85,86],{},[27,87],{"alt":88,"src":89},"Done","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FND1YDpY.png",[17,91,92],{},"Back to Raycast — click \"Setting\" in the bottom-left to open settings:",[17,94,95],{},[27,96],{"alt":97,"src":98},"Setting","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F6BtSEVM.png",[17,100,101],{},"You should land on the \"General\" tab by default. Find \"Raycast Hotkey\" and set it to Cmd + Space.",[17,103,104],{},[27,105],{"alt":106,"src":107},"Raycast Hotkey","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQ0BKE7K.png",[12,109,111],{"id":110},"raycast-ui-tour","Raycast UI tour",[17,113,114],{},"Raycast is English-only, so here's an annotated screenshot for reference:",[17,116,117],{},[27,118],{"alt":119,"src":120},"Raycast labeled UI","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F2fkHp4O.png",[17,122,123],{},[27,124],{"alt":125,"src":126},"Raycast Settings labeled","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fcdup6nS.png",[12,128,130],{"id":129},"raycast-basics","Raycast basics",[17,132,133],{},"Since Raycast is very close to Spotlight, you can use it to launch apps or do quick math out of the box:",[17,135,136],{},[27,137],{"alt":138,"src":139},"Open VSCode","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkDmHuMi.png",[17,141,142],{},[27,143],{"alt":144,"src":145},"Calculator","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbeEAQeZ.png",[17,147,148],{},"So everything you used Spotlight for, Raycast does too — think of it as Spotlight Plus. Now the actually useful tricks.",[150,151,153],"h3",{"id":152},"set-an-alias-for-an-app","Set an alias for an app",[17,155,156],{},"I open Visual Studio Code a lot, so I set an alias for it.",[17,158,159],{},"Open Raycast, go to Settings → \"Extensions\", search \"Visual Studio Code\":",[17,161,162],{},[27,163],{"alt":164,"src":165},"Visual Studio Code","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVaqD94K.png",[17,167,168],{},"Set the Alias to \"vscode\". Now type \"vscode\" in Raycast and it opens Visual Studio Code instantly, and the shortcut shows up in the UI:",[17,170,171],{},[27,172],{"alt":173,"src":174},"vscode alias","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0AGucQE.png",[150,176,178],{"id":177},"set-a-search-provider","Set a search provider",[17,180,181],{},"Another solid feature — search the web directly from Raycast. Just type \"Search Google\" followed by your query, and hit Enter:",[17,183,184],{},[27,185],{"alt":186,"src":187},"Search Google","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FlrgK1Re.png",[17,189,190,191,195],{},"Typing \"Search Google\" every time is awkward, so give it a shortcut. Settings → \"Extensions\", search \"Search Google\", set the alias to \"",[192,193,194],"code",{},"\u002F","\":",[17,197,198],{},[27,199],{"alt":200,"src":201},"Search Google alias","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fi2ncthc.png",[17,203,204,205,207],{},"Now typing \"",[192,206,194],{},"\" followed by your query in Raycast searches Google.",[17,209,210],{},[27,211],{"alt":186,"src":212},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fz3oGRMU.png",[17,214,215],{},"It opens whichever browser you have set as the system default.",[150,217,219],{"id":218},"clipboard-history","Clipboard history",[17,221,222],{},"Raycast also has clipboard history — handy when you want to paste something you copied a while back. Type \"Clipboard\" in Raycast:",[17,224,225],{},[27,226],{"alt":227,"src":228},"Clipboard","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FYilEGM7.png",[17,230,231],{},[27,232],{"alt":233,"src":234},"Clipboard list","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXYlvSYA.png",[17,236,237],{},"Saves you when you copied A, then accidentally copied B and overwrote A. Pretty handy.",[150,239,241],{"id":240},"installing-extensions","Installing extensions",[17,243,244],{},"Beyond Raycast's built-ins, you can install extensions — like Google Translate.",[17,246,247,248,253],{},"Head to the ",[35,249,252],{"href":250,"rel":251},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.raycast.com\u002Fstore",[39],"Raycast Store"," and search \"Google Translate\":",[17,255,256],{},[27,257],{"alt":258,"src":259},"Google Translate","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQW6LLi3.png",[17,261,262],{},"Click \"Install Extension\":",[17,264,265],{},[27,266],{"alt":267,"src":268},"Install Extension","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FkNr31Lr.png",[17,270,271],{},"A welcome popup shows up:",[17,273,274],{},[27,275],{"alt":276,"src":277},"Store welcome","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FoSR21mC.png",[17,279,280],{},"Then the install screen — hit \"Install\":",[17,282,283],{},[27,284],{"alt":285,"src":286},"Install","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FmsbjoXm.png",[17,288,289],{},"Once installed, set up your translation languages. In Raycast type \"Google Translate\", hit Enter:",[17,291,292],{},[27,293],{"alt":294,"src":295},"Google Translate setup","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqcRyP5f.png",[17,297,298],{},"Hit Enter again to open the translation UI, then type the text to translate:",[17,300,301],{},[27,302],{"alt":303,"src":304},"Google Translate UI","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FDcu3FHu.png",[17,306,307,308,311],{},"You can give this an alias too — I set mine to ",[192,309,310],{},"gt",".",[12,313,315],{"id":314},"final-notes","Final notes",[17,317,318],{},"Raycast has way more features than fit in one post — explore on your own from here.",[12,320,322],{"id":321},"my-current-aliases","My current aliases",[17,324,325],{},"For reference, here are the aliases I have set up right now:",[327,328,329,335,341,347,352,358,364,370,376,382],"ul",{},[330,331,332,334],"li",{},[192,333,310],{}," — Google Translate",[330,336,337,340],{},[192,338,339],{},"vscode"," — Visual Studio Code",[330,342,343,346],{},[192,344,345],{},"chrome"," — Google Chrome",[330,348,349,351],{},[192,350,194],{}," — search engine",[330,353,354,357],{},[192,355,356],{},"ff"," — Firefox",[330,359,360,363],{},[192,361,362],{},"cal"," — Calendar",[330,365,366,369],{},[192,367,368],{},"clip"," — Clipboard",[330,371,372,375],{},[192,373,374],{},"todo"," — Todoist",[330,377,378,381],{},[192,379,380],{},"note"," — Notion",[330,383,384,387],{},[192,385,386],{},"sp"," — Spotify",{"title":389,"searchDepth":390,"depth":390,"links":391},"",2,[392,393,394,395,396,403,404],{"id":14,"depth":390,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":390,"text":23},{"id":67,"depth":390,"text":68},{"id":110,"depth":390,"text":111},{"id":129,"depth":390,"text":130,"children":397},[398,400,401,402],{"id":152,"depth":399,"text":153},3,{"id":177,"depth":399,"text":178},{"id":218,"depth":399,"text":219},{"id":240,"depth":399,"text":241},{"id":314,"depth":390,"text":315},{"id":321,"depth":390,"text":322},"Misc","2023-04-12 13:52:33","Raycast is a Mac app that can fully replace Spotlight — and it's way more capable. This post walks through installing Raycast, swapping Spotlight's Cmd+Space hotkey over to Raycast, the basic features (open apps, calculator), setting per-app aliases, using Raycast as a Google search bar, the clipboard history feature, and installing extensions like Google Translate from the Raycast Store.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight","3",{"title":6,"description":407},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight",[29,418,419,420],"Spotlight","Mac","Productivity",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F12\u002Fraycast-replace-mac-spotlight\u002F","_vjPgCV85qyVkd-IQGJJOXxssvTOty-n3xqb6nvHjDk",{"newer":425,"older":429},{"url":426,"title":427,"date":428},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F13\u002Ffree-chatgpt-account-and-prompting-tips\u002F","Use ChatGPT Without Paying or Writing Code (2023 Snapshot)","2023-04-13 21:43:40",{"url":430,"title":431,"date":432},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F04\u002F07\u002Fvite-proxy-fix-cors\u002F","Using Proxy in Vite to Fix CORS Issues","2023-04-07 10:37:57",[434,439,444],{"url":435,"title":436,"date":437,"readingMinutes":438},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":440,"title":441,"date":442,"readingMinutes":443},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":445,"title":446,"date":447,"readingMinutes":448},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784013066702]